    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5129" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κατα-χέω</span></b> , aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κατέχευα</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καταχεῦαι</span>, mid. aor. 3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κατέχυντο</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">pour down, shower down, shed
            over</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί τι</span>); not of
          fluids only, but variously, of letting fall a garment, <i><span class="en">Il. 5.734</span></i>; throwing down wands, <i><span class="en">Il. 6.134</span></i>; levelling a wall, <i><span class="en">Il. 7.461</span></i>; and often metaph., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χάριν, πλοῦτον, ὀνείδεα,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 2.12</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> Β
            670</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 14.38</span></i>; mid.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅπλα εἰς ἄντλον</span>, ‘fell in a heap,’
            <i><span class="en">Od. 12.411</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
